workflow.name: Cluster webpage topics from Google Sheets to Google Sheets for AI discovery

parameters.content:
## üß† Auto-Cluster Topics for AI Discovery

### How it works
This workflow scrapes webpage content from a Google Sheet, uses AI to extract entities and keywords, assigns topical clusters and subclusters, then suggests internal linking opportunities. It's built to strengthen topical authority for LLM-based search engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini.

### Setup steps
1. Connect your Google Sheets OAuth2 credential
2. Connect your OpenAI API credential (uses GPT-4o-mini)
3. Add a Google Sheet with a column named **URL**
4. Replace the document ID and sheet name in "Fetch URL List" and "Update Sheet Row"
5. Run manually or let it trigger weekly via the schedule

## üì• Input & Batch Processing
Fetches URLs from Google Sheets and splits them into batches for sequential processing to avoid rate limits.

## üåê HTML Scraping & Extraction
Fetches the raw HTML and extracts all heading tags (H1‚ÄìH6) to analyze page structure.

## ü§ñ AI-Powered Entity & Keyword Extraction
Uses GPT-4o-mini to analyze headings and extract entities, keywords, topics, and a one-paragraph summary for each page.

## üìÇ Cluster & Subcluster Assignment
Groups pages into high-level clusters and subclusters based on semantic similarity to build topical authority.

## üîó Internal Linking Suggestions
Recommends 3‚Äì5 related URLs from your dataset to strengthen cross-linking and boost AI discoverability.

## üíæ Update Google Sheets
Writes all extracted data, clusters, and link suggestions back to the sheet for easy review and action.

## üîê Credentials & Security
Use OAuth2 for Google Sheets and API keys for OpenAI. Replace sample document IDs and workspace references before deploying.

Your job is to analyze webpage structure and extract semantic signals AI search engines use.

Return ONLY valid JSON matching this exact format:

{
  "title": "string",
  "entities": ["entity1", "entity2"],
  "keywords": ["keyword1", "keyword2"],
  "topics": ["topic1", "topic2"],
  "summary": "one paragraph summary"
}

=You are a topical authority clustering engine.

Assign each page to a high-level cluster and subcluster relevant for LLM search.

Return JSON ONLY:

{
  "cluster": "string",
  "subcluster": "string"
}
